<br>
Scale factor = <strong><sup>5</sup>&frasl;<sub>3</sub></strong>
<br>
(ii)
<br>
Scale factor = <sup>CD</sup>&frasl;<sub>AB</sub>; CD = ?, AB = 4m, scale factor = <sup>5</sup>&frasl;<sub>3</sub>
<br>
<sup>5</sup>&frasl;<sub>3</sub> = <sup>CD</sup>&frasl;<sub>3</sub> cross multiply;
<br>
3 x CD = 5 X 4
<br>
3CD = 20; divide both sides by 3
<br>
<sup>3CD</sup>&frasl;<sub>3</sub> = <sup>20</sup>&frasl;<sub>3</sub>
<br>
CD = <strong>6<sup>2</sup>&frasl;<sub>3</sub>m</strong>
<br>
(iii) 
<br>
The centre of enlargement is; <strong>Point zero(O)</strong>
<br>
<br>
