<br>
(i)
<br>
Scale factor = <sup>OF</sup>&frasl;<sub>OC</sub>; OF = 4 + 2 = 6m, OC = 4m
<br>
Scale factor = <sup>6</sup>&frasl;<sub>4</sub>
<br>
Scale factor = <strong><sup>3</sup>&frasl;<sub>2</sub></strong>
<br>
<strong>Length OD;</strong>
<br>
Scale factor = OD/OA <sup>OD</sup>&frasl;<sub>OA</sub>cross multiply;
<br>
OD = scale factor x OA; scale factor = <sup>3</sup>&frasl;<sub>2</sub>, OA = 10m
<br>
OD = <sup>3</sup>&frasl;<sub>2</sub> X 10
<br>
OD = 3 x 5
<br>
OD = <strong>15m</strong>
<br>
(ii)
<br>
<strong>Length AD;</strong>
<br>
OD = OA + AD; OD = 15m, OA = 10m and AD =?
<br>
15 = 10 + AD
<br>
AD = 15 – 10
<br>
AD = <strong>5m</strong>
